<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>It would appear that many here have different versions of how and when Grimrott spawns in both of his forms.  A mid-level Druid, Cleric and I (34 Paladin) are about to attempt this quest.  When I or the Cleric get the shield, I shall return here to post how we did it.<BR>
<BR>
hehehe...and to that poor individual making the remarks that a Dungeons & Dragons Paladin can have a Choatic Neutral Alignment I have but one suggestion:  Better go back and read your Players Handbook again.  Paladins in AD&D can have NO alignment other than LAWFUL GOOD.  If a paladin does anything that results in an alignment change from Lawful Good to any other alignment he is IMMEDIATELY stripped of all Paladin abilities and becomes a Fighter with Paladin Hit Dice.  <BR>
<BR>
I have played AD&D for 23 years using both 1st and 2nd edition rules.  To my best knowledge 3rd edition has not yet been released (not saying it hasn't...I just have not seen it) and my statements above are in line with the rules for Paladins in both editions.  Perhaps you were thinking of the Cavalier sub-class??</font></td></tr></table>
